name: Superboy Fights the Thought Beast of Krypton!

description: A lunatic has rigged a train to explode, and it's heading for the sleepy town of Mahfoon, Arizona. Only Navajo bounty hunter Sleek Raven can out-race the locomotive and save the town… Arie Kaplan and Robby Musso conclude their stories of past Racers throughout history with a rip-roarin' tale of the Old West.

Reprints political cartoons, Joe Bob Briggs and Ian Shoales columns, and comic strips: Calvin & Hobbes, Outland, Doonesbury, Angriest Dog in the World (David Lynch), and Life In Hell (Matt Groening)

name: Air Hawk : Flying Doctors

description:
Batman: The Return - Planet Gotham

Bruce Wayne is back! And he means business. Dick Grayson is told he must remain as Batman - they need all the Batmen they can get in Bruce's new enterprise - Batman Inc. Later, Damian tracks a new mysterious enemy involved with the Leviathan gang.

Batman Inc #1 - Mr. Unknown Is Dead

Batman begins his international recruitment drive in Japan, with assistance from Catwoman. But when the Bat and Cat arrive in the land of the Rising Sun, they discover the local hero, Mr. Unknown, has been murdered!

Batwoman #0 - Beyond A Shadow

Follow Batman's diary entries to discover the legends that is Kate Kane - a.k.a. Batwoman - the kick-ass, crime-fighting superhero. Her origin story and personal grievances, not forgetting her incredible fight moves are laid bare in this awesome introductory episode.
name: Batman: The Return/Batman Inc #1/Batwoman #0

description:
Which Villain Are You?

The villlains take over in the latest issue of Batman: The Brave And The Bold! Just like super heroes, bad guys come in all shapes and sizes! Have you ever wondered which villain you would be? Take our villain quiz to see just how evil you are!

'Help Wanted' Part One

Two dastardly criminals, Toyman and Clock King, wreak havoc in the latest issue of Batman: The Brave And The Bold! One is a genius inventor of toys, the other uses clock-like gadgetry and bad time jokes. Even Superman can't stop them - so what chance does the Caped Crusader have?

Also inside this issue:

  • Two free mystery gifts!
  • The Criminal's Companion for Causing Chaos
  • The Joker's Episode Guide: Game Over For Owlman!
  • Villain File: Black Manta
  • Learn to Draw Kanjar Ro
  • Pull-out poster
  • Brain-bending puzzles and activities
name: Help Wanted: Part One

volume.name: Batman: The Brave and the Bold

description:
'Help Wanted' Part Two!

After the villains took over in the previous issue of Batman: Brave and the Bold, Batman is back with his super hero teammates to rid the Gotham streets of super-villainy! Check out the awesome climax of 'Help Wanted'!

The Super Hero Handbook

There's nothing more awesome than being a super hero! But fighting crime and protecting the innocent is not a job for the faint of heart. Check out our handy guide to see what it takes to save the world on a regular basis!

The Super Hero Super Quiz!

The super heroes are back and better than ever! Now you've seen what they can do, it's time to test your knowledge of Batman and his teammates in our awesome mega-quiz!

Also inside this issue:

  • Win LEGO DC Super Hero figures
  • Cut out targets to use with your free Joker Punch Gun!
  • Batman's Secret Files: B'Wana Beast
  • Episode Guide: The Fate of Equinox
  • Pull-out poster
  • Brain-bending puzzles and activities
  • Bat-Signals: Your letters and artwork
name: Help Wanted: Part Two

volume.name: Batman: The Brave and the Bold

description:
Justice League - Part 2

The secret origin of the Justice League continues! The odds are stacked against Batman and Green Lantern when Superman attacks! But how will the Man of Steel fare when the Flash enters the fray?

Action Comics: In Chains - Part 2

Superman captured! Eager to experiment on the extraterrestrial, Lex Luthor tests the limits of Superman's powers - with shocking results! What secrets will the evil genius uncover? Whatever you do, Lex, don't make him angry!

Green Lantern: Sinestro - Part 2

With Hal Jordan struggling to adjust to life after the Green Lantern Corps, his former archnemesis, Sinestro, makes him an offer he can't refuse! Meanwhile the Sinestro Corps are on the hunt for their former leader to win the right to control the wielders of the yellow light!
name: Justice League - Part 2/Action Comics: In Chains - Part 2/Green Lantern: Sinestro - Part 2

description:
Kick off the winter blues with a brand-new issue of CLiNT! We've got a barnstorming full issue of Kick-Ass 2, a world exclusive new chapter of Rex Royd, plus 24 thunderous pages of Superior and the final chapter to Who Is Jake Ellis?! Incredible!

  • A massive 22 new pages of Mark Millar's Kick-Ass 2
  • The mayhem of Rex Royd continues with chapter 6 of Frankie Boyle's comic
  • Graveyard of Empires - Part Two of Mark Sable and Paul Azaceta's Afghanistan-set comic
  • Interview with Garth Ennis, writer of Preacher, Hitman, Stitched and many others
  • We salute the unsung heroes of CLiNT with interviews with colourists, letterers and editors
  • Part Eight of Mark Millar's Superior

It’s a bunch of firsts for Kevin Keller in the FIRST issue of his ongoing series. It’s his FIRST time as Riverdale High class president. And he gets published in the Riverdale newspaper for the FIRST time. Oh yeah, and Kevin gets ready to go on his FIRST date! What??!! Kevin’s never been on a date before? That’s the reaction everybody has, as they can’t believe cool, good-looking, mild mannered Kevin Keller has never been on a date. And when he’s made attempts in the past things go terribly wrong…..it turns out Kevin Keller is actually bad at something…..DATING! But the Riverdale gang, along with his old friends and family step in to help ol’ Kevin out. With his friends and family at the helm can anything possibly go wrong? Of course!!! But Kevin will get through it anyway!!!!

Sela has finally found her true love, Prince Eric, trapped in the limbo of Myst.

In order to free his soul she will have to battle not only the Mistress of the realm but her most loyal servant, the terrible and merciless Jack the Giant Killer. 

Note:  Two of the variant covers (snowboards) have no cover information in relation to title, numbering or creators.
name: Lost Souls

description:
Marcus faces off against Taskmaster, Deadpool and the Serpent Society!

The villain that made Marcus the most wanted man in the Marvel Universe is revealed.

The question "Who is Marcus Johnson" is answered, exposing the greatest secret in the Marvel Universe!
Kingpin vs. T'Challa in this status-quo changing series finale! Guest-starring: Lady Bullseye! Typhoid Mary! Falcon! Luke Cage!
name: Reign's End

volume.name: Black Panther: The Most Dangerous Man Alive

description:
Cross returns to Neverland to find the it devastated by a war waged by the mysterious and evil new ruler of the realm.

Known only as the Scourge King, Tiger Lily and her warriors are all that stand between him and the complete destruction of Neverland. Can Cross turn the tide of the battle or will he end up being just be another casualty on the battlefield?

volume.name: Grimm Fairy Tales Presents Neverland: Hook

description:
On the run, with no memory of who they are or where they are going, and being pursued by an unknown enemy, the crew unearths a clue buried deep within the ship's database. Their search for answers leads them to a remote world, an alien threat, and, ultimately, the startling truth about their past!

Fresh off their long tenure on Stargate, Joseph Mallozzi and Paul Mullie create a thrilling new science-fiction universe with kinetic pencils by exciting newcomer Garry Brown!
name: Rebirth, Part 2 of 4

description: The Arc-Ending Issue That Will Leave You Reeling! Elric and Hawkmoon have made their way to Tanelorn to find the seemingly unassailable city under siege. Can they beat back the forces of Chaos that have been threatening their journey all along - and as the forces of Law and Chaos converge, will they finally come face to face with Corum and Eric Beck? Legendary fantasy author Michael Moorcock and New York Times bestseller Chris Roberson bring fantasy's most beloved characters back to comics in this critically acclaimed series!

It's the big showdown between the Kilgore brothers and the swarming hordes of the Second Church in the heart of Radical City! With the help of an enigmatic new ally, Haunt cuts loose on his enemies... but will it be enough to ensure his escape?
name: The Glorious Orgy

first_appearance_locations.name: Radical City of the Second Church

location_credits.name: Radical City of the Second Church

description:
Having gained a new understanding of her affinities for earth, wind, and water, Zoey Redbird moves into more dangerous territory as she attempts to master a lesson in fire. Zoey seeks guidance from the secret vampyre history of Cleopatra and her relationships with two great Roman leaders--Julius Caesar and Mark Antony.

Readers gain knowledge about Zoey's maturation as a fledgling vamp as she becomes the leader of the Dark Daughters.

What do you do when you're ripped from the 21st centuary and thrown into the middle of one of the greatest - and most bloodthirsty - civilizations in human history? How do you survive a strange world of war, blood, sacrifice, and death?

Sam Humphries new 6 issue mini series starts here with Blood Will Tear Us Apart
name: Blood Will Tear us Apart

description:
A brand new story arc begins here! When Jeff finally moved away from his abusive home life, he thought he had escaped the cycle of violence that was his life.

But when his younger brother Drew, commits suicide, Jeff must come back to the one place where he thought he would never return. Meanwhile forces not of this world are slowly shaping Jeff's destiny in terrifying ways... Forces that may very well bring out the Beast within him. The BEAUTY and THE BEAST story arc starts here in what will become one of the most talked about story lines in the Grimm Fairy Tales Universe. 

Note: Samantha Darren appears only on the cover.  An alternate cover is an homage to the fact that Beauty and the Beast is a common Disney on Ice featured skating duo.
name: Beauty and the Beast, Part 1 of 4

description: It ain't over till it's over. Project Next Men has been undone, the Past has been rewritten… but it's never easy to reshape the Fourth Dimension. As Jasmine is about to discover. She was afraid to go with Nathan and Bethany back to the 1950s—by the end of this issue, she may regret that decision!
name: Mosiac

description: Elfheim #1 Volume 1 from 1991.
name: Issue #1

person_credits.name: Barry Blair
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, cover

description: Who are they? How did they come to be dead and/or decapitated? And what kind of brutal insanity is their passing about to unleash? Find out the grim connection between college student Kelly Hara and the ice-cold engine of death known as Varla as the origin of the Ninjettes is revealed.
name: Welcome To Violence

description: The dreaded moon pirates of Mars are whisking John Carter off to a mysterious and surely unpleasant fate. Along for the ride is Phaidor, a thern princess whose beauty is only matched by her complete lack of humanity. As far as Phaidor is concerned, all life on Mars is beneath the therns, but she's going to get a rude awakening about the ugly truth behind the religion she's believed so blindly for her entire existence. Warlord of Mars #15: Issus, Goddess of Life Eternal. Hell hath no fury like a thern princess scorned!
name: Gods of Mars, Part 3: Issus, Goddess of Life Eternal

description:
Betty and Veronica in “The Protector!” – Mr. Lodge’s private screening room has been converted into a silent movie theatre for the kid’s enjoyment! Archie offers his protection to the girls if the horror movie becomes too scary but will Archie be up to the task when the lights go down? And the only thing Mr. Lodge has to beware is Jughead’s monstrous appetite!

Betty in “Rhyme and Reason” – Betty’s baby-sitting gig leads to story time where Betty breathes new life into old nursery rhymes to prove to the young boys she’s sitting that fairy tales aren’t so boring after all!
name: The Protector / Rhyme and Reason

description: “Archie Gets Some Tough Love From Dr. Bill” – Archie is the subject of a television segment “Tough Love” when he visits the Dr. Bill show. The reluctant TV show guest must sweat it out under the studio lights when he’s taken to task by gal pals Betty and Veronica on which of them he will finally choose! What will be Archie’s decision when Dr. Bill poses the ultimate question on national television?
name: Archie Gets Some Tough Love From Dr. Bill
